<subSubSection id="C304FCE67605FFC369901E1616C2FE3F" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA1AF6D7605FFC369901E1616C2FE3F" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7605FFC369901E16135CFE80" bold="true" box="[197,321,267,293]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7605FFC3681C1E11107DFE80" box="[329,608,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigradata">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7605FFC3681C1E11107DFE80" box="[329,608,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Hemipenthes bigradata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7605FFC36BA81E11118FFE80" box="[765,914,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chimaera">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7605FFC36BA81E11118FFE80" box="[765,914,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. chimaera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the presence of yellow and black pile on mesopleuron. The genitalia of both species are clearly different, mainly by the presence of a ventral extension in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1ED4EE7605FFC36B101E4410FBFED7" box="[581,742,345,370]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigradata">
<emphasis id="B96A737F7605FFC36B101E4410FBFED7" box="[581,742,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">H. bigradata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genitalia. The examined specimens are only from 
<collectingCountry id="F309EFFD7605FFC36C0A1E441781FED6" box="[1375,1436,345,371]" name="United States of America" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">USA</collectingCountry>
localities but this species has also been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F309EFFD7605FFC36A5A1E9D1174FE3F" box="[783,873,384,410]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8FD29C7605FFC36A221E9D16CFFE3F" author="Evenhuis" box="[887,1234,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="48" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (1999) World catalog of bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, 756 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Evenhuis &amp; Greathead, 
<number id="3DD6BD4A7605FFC36DC61E9D16CFFE3F" box="[1171,1234,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
